  "slug": "overnight-farmhouse-bread",
  "title": "Overnight Farmhouse Bread",
  "subtitle": "Mostly waiting, mostly worth it.",
  "excerpt": "Overnight Farmhouse Bread. A home-cook's recipe from Rebecca's collection, kept in the family rotation.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook. Bread recipes draw on the long tradition of home baking, Elizabeth David's English Bread and Yeast Cookery is one of the canonical references in English.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Overnight Farmhouse Bread. A British home-cook's dish, the kind of recipe families adjust across generations. Adjustable for what you need.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bread is mostly waiting. Mix, prove, shape, prove again, bake hot with steam.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Strong bread flour",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 3,
              "prepNote": "I used 3 ½ cups",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f2z50002rkv4t08xb4hj",
              "ingredientSlug": "strong-bread-flour"
            },
            {
              "name": "Dried yeast",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 0.25,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f93900avrkv421qf0mr0",
              "ingredientSlug": "yeast-dried"
            },
            {
              "name": "Fine sea salt",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 1.25,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f7kz0086rkv4lsr8ds3o",
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine"
            },
            {
              "name": "Water",
              "unit": "cup",
              "amount": 1.5,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49fbg200evrkv4c5xrql7q",
              "ingredientSlug": "water"
            },
            {
              "name": "Plain flour",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": null,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f2xb0000rkv47vd545ba",
              "ingredientSlug": "plain-flour"
            }
          ],
          "defaultServings": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Mix flour, yeast and salt in a large bowl.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add warm water to the ingredients and mix until a sticky dough forms.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cover with a towel and let it rise on the counter for 12 hours.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Preheat the oven to 500F/260C with the dutch oven inside.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Turn your dough out on a floured surface, it will be flat, tuck all four sides in to form a ball and place it on a floured surface seam side down, sprinkle with more flour and cover with a towel. Don't be afraid to be generous with flour.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Let it rise for 20 minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "If you are short on time you can bake your bread after a 20 minute rise, and it will be a somewhat dense and hefty loaf yet still delicious. (Like mine in the pictures). Alternatively, you can let it rise for 2 more hours in order to produce a more airy loaf of bread.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cut slits in the top of the loaf with a sharp knife approximately 1-2cm deep to allow steam to escape and create a better shaped loaf.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Take the dutch oven out of the oven and carefully place your dough in it, cover with a lid and bake for 25 minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Take the lid off and bake for 10-15 minutes longer to get more colour into your crust.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Note - If the crust colour of your loaf is not as dark after 10-15, increase your oven time for a thicker, deeper coloured crust.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Check yeast in warm water with a pinch of sugar. It should froth in five minutes. Prove in a warm spot (airing cupboard or oven with the light on).",
              "cause": "Yeast was stale, or the dough was too cold.",
              "symptom": "Bread is dense and didn't rise"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Preheat to 220°C with a tray on the bottom. Throw a cup of water into the tray when the loaf goes in, steam gives crust.",
              "cause": "Oven not hot enough, or no steam.",
              "symptom": "Crust is pale and soft"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Give it longer, until the dough doesn't spring back when poked. Shape gently so the bubbles survive.",
              "cause": "Underproved, or the dough was knocked back too hard.",
              "symptom": "Open crumb wasn't open"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Bake on a heavier tray on the middle shelf. Lining with baking paper helps.",
              "cause": "Tray was too thin, or rack too low.",
              "symptom": "Bottom burnt before top browned"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Seeded crust: brush the top with water and roll in mixed seeds before the final prove.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Wholemeal: replace 100 g of the flour with wholemeal for a denser, nuttier loaf.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
